description.text:
Inspired by swiddie's &quot;Makerfarm Prusa i3v one tool bed adjustment bracket&quot; and zapta's &quot;Makerfarm Prusa i3v one tool leveling bracket&quot;  
The current version of the Makerfarm I3v 10&quot; has rounded corners so I decided to create a version of these clips for this model.  Interestingly enough, there are two different corners on my table so I included clips for each type.  Nuts are not held fast within the part to allow for slight variations in nut size but they do work well to hold the nut while adjusting the leveling screw.  There is a small lip on the top to help secure the clip to the table.  
Parts were created in ViaCAD Pro 9 &amp; converted to DXF &amp; STL formats (also included)
